== Milestone titles ==
{{Seealso|List of console game franchises}}
<!--
      PLEASE ADD ALL GAMES IN ALPHABETICAL ORDER
-->
* ''[[BioShock]]'' ([[Microsoft Windows]], PlayStation 3, Xbox 360) is considered a major influential and [[art game|artistic game]] of this generation<ref>[http://www.1up.com/do/reviewPage?cId=3162017 BioShock PC Review Index, BioShock Reviews<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://news.cnet.com/4335-1_105-6587505-1.html Games as art - 'Bioshock' | Crave: The gadget blog<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> with a plot that quickly created controversy with the decisions the player makes during the game.<ref>[http://www.gamepro.com/article/news/130888/bioshock-draws-attention-for-killing-little-girls/ BioShock draws attention for 'killing' little girls | Xbox 360 News | GamePro.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
* ''[[Gears of War]]'' (Microsoft Windows, Xbox 360) had preorder sales which were second only to ''[[Halo 2]]'' in the studio's history.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.edge-online.com/features/gears-war-hype-comes-a-head| title=Gears of War Hype Comes to a Head| date=2006-11-05| first=Kris|last=Graft| publisher=Next-gen.biz| accessdate=2008-07-09}}</ref><!-- Note the original Reuters story is unavailable --> ''Gears of War'' was also the first Xbox or Xbox 360 game to sell out and reach the top ten charts in Japan.<ref>{{cite web | first = Emma | last = Boyes | publisher = [[GameSpot]] | url = http://www.gamespot.com/news/6164717.html | title = Gears of War shoots into Japanese top 10 | accessdate = 2007-01-27 }}</ref> On November 7, 2006<U+2014>the day that it was released<U+2014>it became the most popular game on the [[Xbox Live]] service, overtaking ''Halo 2'', which had held the spot since its launch in November 2004.<ref>{{cite web | title = Gears of War takes top spot in Xbox Live chart | publisher = [[GamesIndustry.biz]] |date=2006-11-20 | accessdate = 2006-11-20 | url = http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/gears-of-war-takes-top-spot-in-xbox-live-chart}}</ref> By January 19, 2007, just ten weeks after its debut, over three million units of the game had been sold.<ref name = GearsJuggernaut>{{cite web | title = Gears of War Juggernauts sells three million units| first = Microsoft Games Studio | publisher = Xbox.com| date = [[2007-01-19]] | accessdate = 2007-01-19 | url = http://www.xbox.com/en-US/community/news/2007/0119-gearsofwarjuggernautcontinues.htm | archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070202034555/http://www.xbox.com/en-US/community/news/2007/0119-gearsofwarjuggernautcontinues.htm | archivedate = 2007-02-02}}</ref>
* ''[[Grand Theft Auto IV]]'' ([[Microsoft Windows]], PlayStation 3, Xbox 360) is a [[Sandbox (video games)|sandbox-style]] [[action-adventure game|action-adventure]] [[video game]] developed by [[Rockstar North]]. A few Hollywood producers have set precedent by beginning to browse video-game release dates to check for conflicts due to ''Grand Theft Auto IV'''s potential harm to the May 2, 2008 release of ''[[Iron Man (film)|Iron Man]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.canada.com/topics/technology/games/story.html?id=00fb5015-0575-4889-817c-c79f4f4cf176&k=64752 |title=Grand Theft Auto could be Hollywood's biggest summer competition |accessdate=2008-04-28 |author=Nick Lewis |date=2008-04-28 |publisher=Canada.com}}</ref> As of October 2008, the PS3 and Xbox 360 version has taken the second and fourth positions of [[Game Rankings]]{{'}} best-rated games of all time, respectively.<ref name=gamerankings/> ''GTA IV'' also shattered worldwide weekly sales records of any entertainment media to date by grossing over $500 million within the first week of its release.
* ''[[Halo 3]]'' (Xbox 360) broke many first day records, including preorders (1.7 million+), and first day sales (US$170 million+), surpassing its predecessor, ''[[Halo 2]]'', in both of these fields.<ref>{{cite press release  | title =Global Entertainment Phenomenon "Halo 3" Records More Than $300 Million in First-Week Sales Worldwide  | publisher =Microsoft Corp.  | date= 2007-10-04  | url =http://www.microsoft.com/presspass/press/2007/oct07/10-04Halo3FirstWeekPR.mspx  | accessdate =2007-11-05  }}</ref><ref> {{cite web| last =Thorsen| first =Tor| title =Halo 3's first-day US haul = $170M| publisher =[[GameSpot]]| date =[[2007-09-26]]| url =http://www.gamespot.com/news/6179914.html| accessdate =2007-12-12}}</ref> It also featured advanced [[artificial intelligence]] (AI) technology for enemies, though the player's allies' intelligence was less refined.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/xbox360/action/halo3/review.html |title=Halo 3 for Xbox 360 Review - Xbox 360 Halo 3 Review |accessdate=2007-09-25 |author=Gerstmann, Jeff  |date=[[2007-09-23]] |work=[[Gamespot]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/821/821911p5.html|title=IGN: ''Halo 3'' Review|author=Goldstein, Hilary|date=[[2007-10-01]]|accessdate=2007-10-02|work=[[IGN]]}}</ref>
* ''[[Metal Gear Solid 4: Guns of the Patriots]]'' (PlayStation 3) was released to critical acclaim, well regarded for its high quality cinematics, engrossing storyline and impressive gameplay mechanics earning a 10 out of 10 from both IGN and GameSpot,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ps3.ign.com/articles/881/881472p1.html |title=Metal Gear Solid 4: Guns of the Patriots Review| date=2008-06-12| first=Jeff| last=Haynes| publisher=IGN| accessdate=2008-07-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.gamespot.com/ps3/adventure/metalgearsolid4/review.html?om_act=convert&om_clk=gssummary&tag=summary;review| title=Metal Gear Solid 4 review| date=2008-06-13| first=Kevin| last=VanOrd| publisher=GameSpot| accessdate=2008-07-09}}</ref> and a 94% Metacritic rating.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/games/platforms/ps3/metalgearsolid4gunsofthepatriots| title=Metal Gear Solid 4: Guns of the Patriots on Metacritic| publisher=Metacritic| accessdate=2008-07-09}}</ref>
* ''[[Super Mario Galaxy]]'' (Wii), currently one of the most critically acclaimed titles of the seventh generation<!-- Do not insert a missing fact template here. Look at the end of the sentence -->, sold more copies in its first week, including over 500,000 in the US, than any other game for the ''Mario'' title in the history of the franchise.<ref>{{cite web| last = Casamassina | first = Matt | title =Galaxy Sells 500,000 in First Week | publisher = IGN| date =[[2007-11-21]]| url =http://wii.ign.com/articles/837/837034p1.html  | accessdate =2007-11-21}}</ref> As of October 2008, it is the third best-reviewed game of all-time, as listed on [[Game Rankings]],<ref name=gamerankings>{{cite web |title=All-Time Top 20 | publisher=[[Game Rankings]] |url=http://www.gamerankings.com/itemrankings/bestworst.asp |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20071021111016/http://www.gamerankings.com/itemrankings/bestworst.asp |archivedate=2007-10-21 |accessdate=2008-10-31}}</ref> along with being the recipient of many game of the year awards.
* ''[[Super Smash Bros. Brawl]]'' (Wii) is a product of [[Nintendo]], with a small portion of content made in cooperation with [[Sega]] and [[Konami]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.smashbros.com/en_us/characters/sonic.html |title=Sonic |accessdate=2007-10-10 |last=Sakurai |first=Masahiro |date=[[2007-10-10]] |work=Smash Bros. DOJO!! |publisher=Smashbros.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://kotaku.com/gaming/nintendo/e306-super-smash-bros-brawl-qa-173071.php|title = E306: Super Smash Bros. Brawl Q&A|accessdate = 2007-09-18|last = Mcwhertor |first = Michael |date = [[2006-05-11]] |publisher = Kotaku}}</ref> It is the third in a [[Super Smash Bros. (series)|series of cross-over fighting games]] and is the first Wii game to strongly support [[online gaming|online play]]. It is also the first in the series to have third-party characters, with the inclusion of [[Solid Snake]] and [[Sonic the Hedgehog]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.smashbros.com/en_us/gamemode/wi-fi/wi-fi01.html|title=Wi-Fi Play|author=Sakurai, Masahiro|date=2007-11-16|publisher=Smash Bros. DOJO!!}}</ref> It dominated sales during its first week in Japan and the United States, selling 820,000 in Japan and becoming the fastest-selling video game in Nintendo of America's history with 1.4 million sold in the US.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamasutra.com/php-bin/news_index.php?story=17272 |title=Nintendo<U+2019>s Brawl Smashes Open Japanese Charts |author=David Jenkins |publisher=[[Gamasutra]] |date=2008-02-07 |accessdate=2008-05-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://kotaku.com/353711/super-smash-bros-brawl-sells-820k-in-its-debut-week |title=Super Smash Bros. Brawl Sells 820K In Its Debut Week |author=Michael McWhertor |publisher=Kotaku |date=2008-02-07 |accessdate=2008-05-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.nintendo.com/whatsnew/detail/AU8xLess7wISKbSMpYCj_HThii8UiBzG |title=Super Smash Bros. Brawl Smashes Nintendo Sales Records |publisher=[[Nintendo]] |date=2008-03-17 |accessdate=2008-08-03}}</ref>
* ''[[Wii Sports]]'' (Wii) has been attributed as a major factor in the Wii's worldwide success.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/wii/sports/wiisports/news.html?sid=6178806| title=Iwata: Wii Sports 2 benched for now|publisher=[[GameSpot]]|date=2007-09-14|accessdate=2008-02-06}}</ref> The game, along with ''[[Wii Fit]]'', has been cited as attracting more casual, female, and elderly gamers.<ref>{{cite web| url= http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/GadgetGuide/wireStory?id=4220585| title=Sony Quarterly Profit Rises 25 Percent|last=Kageyama|first=Yuri|publisher=[[ABC News]]|date=2008-01-31|accessdate=2008-03-10}}</ref> This is a rarity among seventh generation games, as developers tend to try and attract young men.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,226255,00.html|title="Bully" video games feature boys fighting|publisher=[[FOX News]]|accessdate=2008-05-24}} (Sentence: Most video games target a young male audience and focus on shooting, racing or sports.)</ref> It has also been cited as one game that can provide a bonding experience among family members,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/wireStory?id=3287598| title=Fathers and Kids Bond Over Video Games|last=Slagle|first=Matt|date=2007-06-12|publisher=[[ABC News]]|accessdate=2008-02-05}}</ref> and as a means of exercising and losing weight when played regularly.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.gamespot.com/wii/sports/wiisports/news.html?sid=6166231|title=Study: Wii kids lose weight|last=Boyes|first=Emma| publisher=[[GameSpot]]|date=2007-02-22|accessdate=2008-02-06}}</ref> As of March 31, 2009, the game has sold {{nowrap|45.71 million}} copies worldwide<U+2014>including bundled copies, making it the [[List of best-selling video games#Wii|best-selling Wii game]] and the best-selling video game of all time.<ref>{{cite web |first=Tom |last=Ivan |title=Wii Sports The Best Selling Game Ever? |url=http://www.edge-online.com/news/wii-sports-the-best-selling-game-ever |archiveurl= |work=Edge Online |publisher=Future US |date=2009-05-08 |month= |year= |archivedate= |accessdate= |quote=When approached, however, Nintendo UK said that it couldn<U+2019>t confirm that sales of Wii Sports had overtaken those of Super Mario Bros.}}</ref>
